result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:53 AM Prosecuting attorney Jedidiah J Dodge in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Tyler J Bablitch in court, in custody.  Attorney Oren Jakobson in court for Tyler J Bablitch. 
All files heard:  20CF287, 20CF395, 21CF301, 21CF324, 21CF372, 21CF466, 22CF29, 22CM2

Court addresses 22CF29 has not had a preliminary hearing.  Court questions Atty Jakobson if the defendant would be waiving the preliminary hearing in that file. 
Atty Jakobson states based on the agreement, he will waive that preliminary hearing.  Stipulates to probable cause on that file. 
Court notes there was an information that has been filed and is identical to the charges in the criminal complaint.  
Defendant received copy of information.
Defendant waives reading of information. 
State has complied with Victim Notification Statutes.
There are no victims present today either in person or via zoom. 

Plea Questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.  Uncharged read-in for felony bail jumping with a March 16, 2022 offense date. 
Atty Jakobson concurs with agreement stated but states 2 changes that he had not included on the plea questionnaire.  They are not contesting the restitution that has been requested. 

Defendant enters a plea of: 
21CF466 Count 1 - NO CONTEST
21CF372 Count 1 - NO CONTEST
21CF301 Count 1 - NO CONTEST
20CF287 Count 1 - NO CONTEST

Court questions defendant regarding plea questionnaire, waiver of constitutional rights and understandings.
Court advises defendant of elements the state must prove for the charge.
Court questions attorney for the defendant.
Court finds defendant's plea is freely, voluntarily, knowingly, and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty of 
21CF466 Count 1 - Possession of Narcotic Drugs
21CF372 Count 1 - Felony Bail Jumping
21CF301 Count 1 - Maintaining a Drug Trafficking Place
20CF287 Count 1 - Strangulation/Suffocation as a Domestic
Clerk directed to enter judgment of convictions this date.

Atty Dodge makes sentencing arguments to the court. 
Court questions Atty Jakobson regarding the sentence credit.  
Atty Jakobson responds. 
Atty Dodge makes statements to the court. 
Atty Jakobson states he has contacted the jail and has all the dates he served. 
Atty Jakobson makes sentencing arguments to the court. 
Court questions the defendant. 
Defendant responds. 
Court questions attorneys.

BY THE COURT: 
21CF372 Count 1 - 
Serve 120 days jail. 
126 days credit. 
Time served. 
Pay costs within the next 60 days to the Clerk of Courts office directly or set up a payment plan.
Provide a DNA sample. 
Pay the DNA surcharge. 

Other 3 charges: 
Sentence withheld
Placed on probation for a period of 36 months: 
Participate in a drug and alcohol assessment and comply with any recommendations thereof.
Complete any treatment or counseling deemed appropriate by the agent and follow thru.
No controlled substances without a valid prescription and take only as prescribed. 
All prescriptions must be thru one pharmacy.
Sign release to allow the agent to monitor his prescriptions. 
Pay restitution of $80 for 22CM2. 
Not be in the presence of anyone using or consuming controlled substances illegally. 
Pay costs to the probation agent. 
Provide a DNA sample
Pay DNA surcharge

Court questions Atty Dodge regarding his position on the 126 days credit on the remaining 3 files. 
Atty Dodge responds and states statutes. 
Court asks that each attorney send a letter in the next 30 days on sentence credit on the 3 remaining cases.  Court will then review and respond either with a letter or a directive to the Clerk of Court. 
Defendant is to go check in with probation and parole immediately.
Court informs the defendant he will need to pay the costs on 21CF372 directly to the clerk so he will have 2 places to pay.

The following are dismissed and read-in:
22CF29 all counts
22CM2 all counts
21CF466 counts 2 thru 6
21CF372 count 2
21CF324 all counts
21CF301 count 2 
20CF395 all counts
20CF287 counts 2 & 3
S22-02227 is dismissed and read-in
Plea/sentencing hearing on June 29, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Judge Patricia Baker Assigned
/s/ LJM 6/22/2022 - Approved.
